OVERVIEW & PURPOSE
To help students of PGDAC course to prepare well for their exams.
Preparation Strategy / Steps

1. Reading/ Understanding
2. Programming Practise
3. MCQS
Identifying the important topics
1. Go through the syllabus of each module.
2. Segregate the topics session wise.
3. Divide the number of Questions by total number of sessions. The result is the total number of Qs from each session. Example: Module has 20 Sessions, there 40/20= 2. Means each session will contribute to 2 Qs.
4. Focus on the most important concepts of each session and master them. Means - concepts + application in programs + MCQ ( from sanfoundry + Google topic name MCQ). 
